g or changing its direction."},{"version":"blue","text":"Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction."},{"version":"yellow","text":"Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid."},{"version":"gold","text":"With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn't mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains."},{"version":"silver","text":"A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path."},{"version":"crystal","text":"It travels by rol\u00ad ling on mountain paths. If it gains too much speed, it stops by running into huge rocks."},{"version":"ruby","text":"GRAVELER grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This POK\u00e9MON eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"Rocks are GRAVELER\u2019s favorite food. This POK\u00e9MON will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom."},{"version":"emerald","text":"They descend from mountains by tumbling down steep slopes. They are so brutal, they smash aside obstructing trees and massive boulders with thunderous tackles."},{"version":"firered","text":"Be careful while hiking on mountain trails. GRAVELER may come rolling down the path without slowing."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction."},{"version":"diamond","text":"GRAVELER make their homes on sheer cliff faces by gouging out numerous horizontal holes."},{"version":"pearl","text":"It tumbles down slopes, heedless of any body parts chipping off. It eats a ton of rocks daily."},{"version":"platinum","text":"It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pok\u00e9mon can stop it without difficulty."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn\u2019t mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path."},{"version":"black","text":"It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pok\u00e9mon can stop it without difficulty."},{"version":"white","text":"It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pok\u00e9mon can stop it without difficulty."},{"version":"black-2","text":"It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pok\u00e9mon can stop it without difficulty."},{"version":"white-2","text":"It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pok\u00e9mon can stop it without difficulty."},{"version":"x","text":"With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn\u2019t mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains."},{"version":"y","text":"Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pok\u00e9mon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Rocks are Graveler\u2019s favorite food. This Pok\u00e9mon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom."},{"version":"sun","text":"Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly."},{"version":"moon","text":"This slow-footed Pok\u00e9mon moves by curling up and rolling instead of walking. With enough momentum, its speed can exceed 60 mph."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp."},{"version":"lets-go-pikachu","text":"Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid."},{"version":"lets-go-eevee","text":"Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid."},{"version":"legends-arceus","text":"Dwells in holes dug into sheer walls of stone. It enjoys rolling down slopes as though it were a boulder during a rockfall, so keep an eye upward while traversing mountain roads."}],"evo":{"name":"geodude","level":0,"min_level":null,"trigger":null,"item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":null,"turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[{"name":"graveler","level":1,"min_level":25,"trigger":"level-up","item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":"","turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[{"name":"golem","level":2,"min_level":null,"trigger":"trade","item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":"","turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[]}]}]},"sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/75.png","shiny":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/shiny/75.png","capture":120,"happiness":70,"growth":"medium-slow","gender":4,"hatch":15,"ev":{"defense":2},"forms":[{"id":10110,"name":"graveler-alola","sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/10110.png"}]}